label: comparisonOperatorCode
comment: A code specifying the operator, such as, less than, greater than or equal to, for comparing two actual measures.
The code specifying the operator, such as less than, for comparing this inspection result characteristic with one or more other characteristics.
The code specifying the operator, such as less than, greater than or equal to, for comparing the measured value for this sample observation result characteristic.

domainIncludes.comment: A property of a collection of diagnostic data, visual or technical data, obtained by a performed inspection.
An amount, size, or extent as established by measuring.
Specifies the type of the performed observation and the acquired values of this observation on the sample.
